BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:rfKwiiOSCMQ3okI8NcK91
SUMMARY:Jazz Month Tour
DTSTAMP:20260325T052416Z
DTSTART:20260327T143000Z
DESCRIPTION:March’s Women in Jazz Month comes alive as award-winning singer
	-songwriter Eugenie Jones lights up the Royal Room with her national Women
	 in Jazz Month Tour. With stops in Denver\, San Francisco\, Atlanta\, and 
	Seattle\, this tour joins a worldwide tribute to the women who shaped jazz
	\, honoring trailblazers such as Billie Holiday\, Nina Simone\, and Ella F
	itzgerald. At the Royal Room\, Jones will blend beloved songs from female 
	jazz legends\, her own Jazz Week \\#4 ranked originals\, imaginative spins
	 on vintage jazz\, and timeless rhythm and blues classics. She’ll be joine
	d by the remarkable talents of pianist Peter Adams\, bassist Osama Afifi\,
	 and drummer Maria Wulff. As a Seattle Jazz Hall of Fame inductee\, the fi
	rst vocal recording artist to receive Earshot Jazz’s Album of the Year awa
	rd\, a two-time Vocalist of the Year winner\, and a Jazz Journalists Assoc
	iation’s Jazz Hero Award winner\, Jones has received high praise for her v
	ocal prowess. Paris Move magazine describes Jones as “One of the most beau
	tiful voices in the United States\; a consummate interpreter who slips eff
	ortlessly into the soul of her songs.” Preview Jones’ music\, watch videos
	\, or learn more about this gifted entertainer at  https://ffm.to/eugeniej
	onesmusic. Get your tickets today for this unforgettable night of exquisit
	e vocals\, masterful musicianship\, and stirring storytelling\, all in tri
	bute to the enduring legacy and vibrant contributions of women in jazz. Ti
	ckets:  https://www.strangertickets.com/events/180924339/eugenie-jones\n\n
	https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/jazz-month-tour/18252356/202
	6-03-27T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/jazz-month-tour/18252356/
	2026-03-27T00
LOCATION:The Royal Room\, 5000 Rainier Ave South\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-arts
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
